result.execSummary:
Donovan C. Chandler was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Donovan C. Chandler was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
12:59 PM Defendant Donovan C. Chandler appeared by video, in custody from the Jackson County Jail, Attorney Crystal Leigh Jensen appeared in court for State of Wisconsin.
Court advised the defendant of his right to an attorney and hearing. No threats or promises made waive extradition. Defendant wishes to waive extradition.  Defendant signed the waiver in custody.  Court ordered the same.

If revoked and finished sentence and still in custody in JC, defendant is to notify the court for a hearing.
